Interface TreeNode

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNode, GroupNode, LeafNode

    public interface TreeNode
    This class represents a class that will create a list using nodes setup as a tree.

      • checkNode

        TreeNode checkNode(char code)
        Check the children of the current node to see if they contain a character. Returns the node if that node exists, otherwise returns nothing.
        Parameters:
        code - The code to check for.
        Returns:
        Returns the child node if it contains the code, or empty if there is none.

      • getSymbol

        java.lang.Character getSymbol()
        Get the symbol for that node. If it is not a leaf node then it will return null.
        Returns:
        Returns the symbol as a character or null if it is not a leaf node.

      • checkNumberofNodes

        boolean checkNumberofNodes(int compare)
        Check the number of children for the node and compares it to a number. It will return a true if the number of children matches, or false if it doesn't.
        Parameters:
        compare - The number to compare to.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the number of nodes matches.
